# 2. 圧倒的な光

Models: Pardon us.
Staff Member: Ah, come in. Please find a seat along the wall according to your number.
Shizuku: (I was under the impression that we'd be called one at a time, but I guess they're having us audition in groups...)
Shizuku: (I see three judges... One appears to be from Gran Fleur, another from the production company and...)
Shizuku: (Huh...?)
Judges: ...
Shizuku: (That person seems awfully familiar...)
Shizuku: (Oh...!)
Oikawa: Alright, it's great that you have a lot of presence, but I think you're going a bit overboard.
Oikawa: So, try instead to stand out less. How about you turn around and look over your shoulder? Your side profile's enough.
Shizuku: O-Of course...!
Shizuku: (It's Mr. Oikawa...! He helped me so much when he was the creative director for Cheerful * Days.)
Shizuku: (He's become so famous within the industry that some call him the “big hit machine”.)
Shizuku: (This means I have to do my best today to win his approval...!)
Staff Member: Alright, let's get this audition started.
Staff Member: First, this commercial is going to require two people. As such, two will be selected in the end.
Staff Member: Now, we will be looking for you to be “overwhelmingly brilliant”.
Shizuku: (Overwhelmingly brilliant... That's the tagline from the document we received.)
Staff Member: We'll be using the front camera to take shots from afar and up close. Please pose accordingly based on each situation.
Shizuku: (Regardless of how many times I've done this before, expressing myself while standing motionless is still incredibly challenging for me...)
Shizuku: (But I need to strike the perfect poses here!)
Staff Member: Alright, we'll start with number eleven. Please come forward.
Model #11: That's me...!
Model #11: Number eleven, Tomomi Yuki. Thank you for having me.
Shizuku: (It's begun...)
Shizuku: (We're starting by shooting from a distance...)
Model #11: ...
Shizuku: (Oh...)
Shizuku: (She's very good... Her core seems so solid, and her pose is refined...)
Shizuku: (In particular, the way she's lifting her hair. She's making it so the viewers' eyes are naturally drawn to her own.)
Staff Member: Next, the camera will be moving in for a close-up.
Model #11: Ready!
Shizuku: (Her facial expression is mesmerizing... She seems so strong and composed.)
Staff Member: Okay. Would either of you like to see her do any other poses?
Oikawa: Hmm... Nothing from me.
Director: Me as well... I think I've seen enough.
Shizuku: (What...?)
Shizuku: (They don't sound all that satisfied... But I thought she did such a beautiful job...)
Staff Member: Unfortunately, Ms. Yuki, that will be it for you. Thank you for coming.
Model #11: Thank you again for having me...
Shizuku: (This audition is going to be much more difficult than I expected...)
Yu: ...
Oikawa: Hmm... Stop there.
Quiet Model: Okay... Thank you for having me.
Shizuku: (I thought she also did a wonderful job... But the bar they've set seems to be very high.)
Shizuku: (Still, I've done everything possible to prepare for this day. I just need to believe in myself and strike the best poses I can.)
Staff Member: Next, number fourteen, please come forward.
Shizuku: Of course.
Oikawa: Oh, Hinomori, you're next?! I'm ready to get totally blown away by you.
Shizuku: Th-Thank you very much!
Shizuku: (Mr. Oikawa remembered who I am.)
Shizuku: (Which means I can't afford to let him down...!)
Shizuku: Number fourteen, Shizuku Hinomori. Thank you for having me.
Shizuku: (First, I'll be posing from a distance.)
Shizuku: (Their new line of eye shadows are slightly more intense than normal and include lamé... They're Gran Fleur's most showy yet.)
Shizuku: (Coupled with their “overwhelmingly brilliant” tagline, the makers must be trying to say...)
Shizuku: (“Have confidence in yourself.” That has to be what they want the wearers of this eye shadow to feel.)
Shizuku: (Which means...)
Shizuku: (I need to look proud and confident. Puff out your chest and stand tall...!)
Director: ...! Shizuku Hinomori really has a brilliance to her.
Oikawa: ...
Staff Member: Next, we'll move in for a close-up.
Shizuku: Understood!
Shizuku: (I'll need to come up with an even better expression for my close-up.)
Shizuku: (In order for me to put on a proud and confident expression, then I need to...)
Director: Interesting. What a captivating gaze.
Oikawa: Yes, it's not bad...
Oikawa: But...
Oikawa: Something seems different about you, Hinomori.
Shizuku: Huh? Different...?
Oikawa: Hmm... No, nevermind. Anyway, could you give us a different angle?
Shizuku: Y-Yes, of course...!
Director: Ah, that's also a nice expression. It encapsulates the tagline very nicely.
Shizuku: Th-Thank you very much...!
Shizuku: (But...)
Oikawa: ...
Shizuku: (Mr. Oikawa still seems unsatisfied.)
Shizuku: (Am I missing something...? What is it that I'm failing to capture...?)
Shizuku: (Also, what did he mean by me being different...?)
Staff Member: We'll have you stop here, Ms. Hinomori. Thank you very much.
Shizuku: Y-Yes... Thank you for having me.
Staff Member: Next, number fifteen, please come forward.
Yu: Okay.
Shizuku: (Oh, Hagiyama...)
Yu: Number fifteen, Yu Hagiyama.
Yu: Thank you for having me.
Oikawa: Oh...?
Shizuku: (Hagiyama's expression just changed...)
Shizuku: (She has a much stronger and sharper look on her face now...)
Staff Member: We'll be starting from afar. Please pose when you're ready.
Yu: Okay.
Yu: ...
Shizuku: ...!
Shizuku: (I can't look away from her...!)
Shizuku: (Her pose is astonishingly simple... All she did was shift her weight onto one leg.)
Shizuku: (But...)
Shizuku: (Her eyes are so powerful...!)
Shizuku: (The combination of her sharp gaze and natural pose gives her an overwhelming amount of presence.)
Shizuku: (She isn't pandering or yielding to anyone. She's as good as saying it out loud.)
Oikawa: This is good...
Oikawa: Can you give us a different angle, Hagiyama?
Yu: Of course!
Shizuku: (Now I see...)
Shizuku: (Now I know what I was missing. It was this...)
Shizuku: (This painfully bright light...)
Shizuku: ...
Shizuku: (It really is blinding...)
